## Acknowledgement Scan

Acknowledgement Scan:
- Prior-disclosure grep scope: <<grep_scope|github PRs + issues + audit PDFs + post-mortems + fix-commit log (last 90d) + Discord/TG public statements|enumerate which channels were scanned: GitHub PRs/issues, audit PDFs in audit/prior_audits/, post-mortems, fix-commit history window N commits, public Discord/Telegram, etc.>>
- Acknowledgement hits found: <<ack_hits|none|list any prior disclosure that touches the same bug class / call site / root cause. Format: "<source>:<id>:<one-line summary>". If 0 hits, state "none">>
- Distinction from acknowledged variants (R31 prior-concerns separation): <<distinction_from_acknowledged|<distinction prose>|for each acknowledgement hit, cite the precise distinction that makes THIS finding novel: different call site, different bug class, different attack vector, different impact, post-acknowledgement code change reintroduced the bug, etc.>>
- Acknowledged-by-design risk: <<ack_by_design_risk|low|low | medium | high - does the team have a public statement classifying this behavior as intentional? If high, R45 designed-as-intended precheck is mandatory>>
- Fix-commit collision check: <<fix_commit_collision|none|did any post-audit-pin commit fix this bug? If yes, cite the commit SHA + PR number and explain whether the audit-pin code is still exploitable>>
- Verdict: <<r47_verdict|no-prior-acknowledgement|no-prior-acknowledgement | acknowledged-with-distinction | acknowledged-no-distinction (walk back / drop) | acknowledged-but-not-fixed (still fileable)>>

